 After ELISA-testing for P-PG I, p-PG II, P-G-17 and P-Hp-Ab in a plasma sample, an endoscopic examination can be preserved only for those patients whose GastroPanel test results suggest AG, whereas an endoscopic examination can be avoided in subjects with negative GastroPanel result, or in whom the test biomarkers indicate a non-atrophic gastritis or a healthy stomach (18).

